cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "PlantCyc to WikiPathways: BioCyc flat-file to GPML2021 conversion pipeline"
abstract: >
  A pipeline to convert BioCyc/PlantCyc pathway data (BioCyc flat-file format)
  to GPML2021 (Graphical Pathway Markup Language) for upload to WikiPathways.
authors:
  - family-names: Del Pup
    given-names: Elena
    affiliation: "Wageningen University & Research"
    email: elena.delpup@wur.nl
  - family-names: Muller
    given-names: Max
    affiliation: "Wageningen University & Research"
license: AGPL-3.0
repository-code: "https://github.com/pathway-lod/Cyc_to_wiki"
doi: 10.5281/zenodo.18404067
keywords:
  - WikiPathways
  - GPML
  - PlantCyc
  - BioCyc
  - pathway conversion
  - plant metabolism
notes: >
  Development of this software involved assistance from AI tools (Anthropic Claude Code,
  Opus, and Sonnet 4.5/4.6). These tools were used to speed up development, provide
  debugging suggestions, and help structure portions of the code. All AI-generated
  content was thoroughly reviewed, verified, and refined by the authors.
